6. Use Container Widget with color property in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Container widget in Flutter can use the color property to set the background color of the container.
It is useful for:

Styling UI components
Highlighting sections
Improving visual appearance

//main code

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: ContainerColorExample(),
    );
  }
}

class ContainerColorExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Container Color Example"),
      ),
      body: Center(
        child: Container(
          color: Colors.blue,
          height: 100,
          width: 200,
          child: Center(
            child: Text(
              "Colored Container",
              style: TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
            ),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}